00:00:01.001 --> 00:00:03.203 line:5%,start
ABBY LEE MILLER (VOICEOVER):
Previously on "Dance Moms."

00:00:03.269 --> 00:00:04.104 line:5%,start
Line up, soldiers.

00:00:04.170 --> 00:00:06.006 line:5%,start
I don't think some of you want to be here,

00:00:06.072 --> 00:00:09.142 line:5%,start
and I certainly don't think
any of you work hard enough.

00:00:09.209 --> 00:00:12.045 line:5%,start
I can't believe you were tattle-telling
on a seven-year-old.

00:00:12.112 --> 00:00:13.613 line:5%,start
People know how my child dances.

00:00:13.680 --> 00:00:16.049 line:5%,start
Do you really think anyone who
goes to the dance competition

00:00:16.116 --> 00:00:18.051 line:5%,start
knows how your child dances?

00:00:18.251 --> 00:00:20.754 line:5%,start
ABBY LEE MILLER: Kendall,
you're chasing her.

00:00:20.820 --> 00:00:23.990 line:5%,start
Second place, entry number 74,
"Free the People."

00:00:24.057 --> 00:00:26.693 line:5%,start
Sometimes you have nothing intelligent
to say, you should just be quiet.

00:00:26.760 --> 00:00:29.896 line:5%,start
ABBY LEE MILLER: So today, you will
be voting on Maddie or Chloe.

00:00:29.963 --> 00:00:31.231 line:5%,start
Maddie wins.

00:00:31.664 --> 00:00:33.199 line:5%,start
ABBY LEE MILLER (VOICEOVER):
Coming up on "Dance Moms."

00:00:33.299 --> 00:00:35.802 line:5%,start
We're getting beat by teachers
that I've never even heard of before.

00:00:35.869 --> 00:00:36.803 line:5%,start
Here it comes.

00:00:36.903 --> 00:00:37.737 line:5%,start
Whoo.

00:00:37.804 --> 00:00:39.639 line:5%,start
But it's not funny
or cute to throw a kid on stage

00:00:39.706 --> 00:00:40.907 line:5%,start
and them not be warmed up.

00:00:40.974 --> 00:00:44.310 line:5%,start
I have been officially invited
to be on "The View."

00:00:44.377 --> 00:00:46.179 line:5%,start
[applause]

00:00:46.246 --> 00:00:47.747 line:5%,start
My foot doesn't hurt anymore.

00:00:47.814 --> 00:00:48.648 line:5%,start
And?

00:00:48.715 --> 00:00:51.117 line:5%,start
It's about this whole charade.
Don't let her rehearse.

00:00:51.184 --> 00:00:52.218 line:5%,start
- What charade?
- The charade about the foot.

00:00:52.285 --> 00:00:53.820 line:5%,start
What the [bleep] is wrong with the foot?

00:00:53.887 --> 00:00:56.222 line:5%,start
I want to know where the miracle
came from, because--

00:00:56.289 --> 00:00:57.257 line:5%,start
She rested.

00:00:57.323 --> 00:00:59.893 line:5%,start
Don't take it out on me that Abby
pulled your kid from a dance.

00:00:59.959 --> 00:01:02.028 line:5%,start
Why don't you call
the [bleep] doctor and ask him?

00:01:02.095 --> 00:01:04.531 line:95%,end
[MUSIC - NIKKO LOWE, "LIVING ON
THE DANCE FLOOR"]

00:01:04.597 --> 00:01:05.598 line:95%,end
Get up.

00:01:06.099 --> 00:01:07.600 line:95%,end
Get on the floor.

00:01:08.001 --> 00:01:13.473 line:95%,end
My world is with my girls
living on the dance floor.

00:01:14.507 --> 00:01:16.242 line:95%,end
[music continuing]

00:01:18.878 --> 00:01:20.346 line:5%,start
ABBY LEE MILLER: Let's go. Let's go.
Let's go.

00:01:20.413 --> 00:01:21.748 line:5%,start
Come on, girls. Get in here.

00:01:22.282 --> 00:01:25.151 line:95%,end
On the presidential campaign,
this means peace.

00:01:25.218 --> 00:01:27.787 line:95%,end
But here at Abby League Dance Company,
it means seconds.

00:01:28.254 --> 00:01:34.060 line:95%,end
Not only are we getting beat
by Kathy's brilliant team of imports,

00:01:34.127 --> 00:01:37.464 line:95%,end
we're getting beat by teachers
that I've never even heard of before.

00:01:38.231 --> 00:01:39.232 line:95%,end
We were the losers.

00:01:39.299 --> 00:01:43.136 line:95%,end
ALDC lost again, two weeks in a row.

00:01:43.837 --> 00:01:45.271 line:5%,start
How are we going to recover?

00:01:45.939 --> 00:01:48.608 line:5%,start
How are these dancers going to get better?

00:01:48.675 --> 00:01:50.844 line:95%,end
How do they improve in a week?

00:01:51.544 --> 00:01:53.179 line:95%,end
Put the effort forth.

00:01:53.580 --> 00:01:54.881 line:95%,end
You get out what you put in.

00:01:54.948 --> 00:01:56.916 line:5%,start
All right, I want to get to the pyramid.

00:01:57.450 --> 00:01:59.285 line:95%,end
First, I have Mackenzie.

00:01:59.385 --> 00:02:00.286 line:95%,end
You didn't dance.

00:02:00.353 --> 00:02:02.555 line:95%,end
Next, Paige.

00:02:02.956 --> 00:02:06.659 line:95%,end
That flag was a symbol
for everybody in that audience.

00:02:07.293 --> 00:02:09.329 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:02:13.800 --> 00:02:16.836 line:95%,end
Don't do a disservice to this country.

00:02:17.971 --> 00:02:20.073 line:5%,start
Abby puts Paige at the bottom
of the pyramid

00:02:20.140 --> 00:02:23.343 line:5%,start
because she held the flag
upside down the wrong way.

00:02:23.409 --> 00:02:26.212 line:95%,end
That's why we didn't win because Paige
held the flag the wrong way.

00:02:26.279 --> 00:02:28.515 line:95%,end
And next, Kendall.

00:02:29.482 --> 00:02:31.417 line:95%,end
We've worked on your facial expressions.

00:02:31.484 --> 00:02:32.752 line:95%,end
They've improved.

00:02:32.819 --> 00:02:34.487 line:95%,end
We've worked on your stamina.

00:02:34.554 --> 00:02:35.889 line:95%,end
That's getting there.

00:02:36.222 --> 00:02:37.957 line:95%,end
Now focus.

00:02:38.158 --> 00:02:41.294 line:95%,end
Wherever your eyes go,
that's where the judges' eyes go.

00:02:41.594 --> 00:02:46.132 line:95%,end
You can't watch Maddie
like a member of the audience.

00:02:46.199 --> 00:02:48.735 line:95%,end
And next I have Brooke.

00:02:49.636 --> 00:02:52.539 line:95%,end
Brooke, during rehearsal,
you did an outstanding job.

00:02:52.605 --> 00:02:56.276 line:95%,end
Then we get on stage
and you go right by Asia and the flag

00:02:56.342 --> 00:02:58.244 line:95%,end
and then you have to wait four counts.

00:02:59.312 --> 00:03:01.314 line:95%,end
You have to think on stage.

00:03:02.549 --> 00:03:03.483 line:95%,end
Chloe.

00:03:03.550 --> 00:03:05.185 line:95%,end
Chloe, you did a solo.

00:03:05.251 --> 00:03:06.553 line:95%,end
You did a nice job.

00:03:06.619 --> 00:03:08.588 line:95%,end
You were second only to Maddie.

00:03:08.655 --> 00:03:09.956 line:95%,end
Corrections.

00:03:10.023 --> 00:03:11.457 line:95%,end
Hyperextending the elbows.

00:03:11.524 --> 00:03:13.459 line:95%,end
Not lengthening the back of the knee.

00:03:13.526 --> 00:03:18.097 line:95%,end
You can fix all of those things,
but you have to want to.

00:03:18.164 --> 00:03:20.567 line:95%,end
And next, Nia.

00:03:20.633 --> 00:03:21.935 line:95%,end
You did an outstanding job.

00:03:22.001 --> 00:03:23.303 line:95%,end
I thought you looked good in the group.

00:03:23.369 --> 00:03:24.470 line:95%,end
I noticed you in the group.

00:03:24.537 --> 00:03:26.673 line:95%,end
I also noticed that you were smart

00:03:26.739 --> 00:03:30.543 line:95%,end
and you figured out you couldn't
live Asia until she got there.

00:03:30.610 --> 00:03:32.545 line:5%,start
Finally Abby notices Nia.

00:03:32.612 --> 00:03:34.914 line:5%,start
She's making it to the middle
row of the pyramid.

00:03:34.981 --> 00:03:36.216 line:5%,start
That's a good thing.

00:03:37.050 --> 00:03:38.751 line:5%,start
And next.


00:03:38.818 --> 00:03:42.355 line:95%,end
Asia, you won the overall
high score in the petite division.

00:03:43.156 --> 00:03:46.192 line:95%,end
I think that you're a little firecracker,

00:03:46.259 --> 00:03:50.063 line:95%,end
and I think you step on stage
and you cause an explosion.

00:03:50.129 --> 00:03:51.431 line:95%,end
So Asia's number 2.

00:03:51.497 --> 00:03:55.368 line:5%,start
I'll take the 2 for this time, as long as
she doesn't drop lower than that.

00:03:55.802 --> 00:03:58.338 line:95%,end
And on top of the pyramid.

00:03:58.404 --> 00:04:01.541 line:95%,end
Maddie, you were the overall high scorer

00:04:01.608 --> 00:04:02.775 line:95%,end
of the junior division.

00:04:03.009 --> 00:04:05.778 line:95%,end
And in first place, entry number 30,
"I'm Trying."

00:04:05.845 --> 00:04:08.147 line:95%,end
- Yeah, Maddie.
- Whoo-hoo.

00:04:08.514 --> 00:04:10.283 line:95%,end
Your friends voted for you, too.

00:04:10.350 --> 00:04:11.484 line:95%,end
It was a good performance.

00:04:11.551 --> 00:04:16.055 line:5%,start
You are the type of personality
that this country was built on.

00:04:16.789 --> 00:04:18.858 line:95%,end
You all know that song
"America the Beautiful?"

00:04:18.925 --> 00:04:21.327 line:95%,end
Maddie, you are America the Beautiful.

00:04:22.128 --> 00:04:22.929 line:5%,start
You're welcome.

00:04:22.996 --> 00:04:25.198 line:95%,end
People have accused me
of playing favorites.

00:04:25.265 --> 00:04:27.634 line:95%,end
Maddie gets what she deserves.

00:04:27.700 --> 00:04:29.035 line:95%,end
She puts in the time.

00:04:29.102 --> 00:04:30.236 line:95%,end
She puts in the energy.

00:04:30.303 --> 00:04:31.638 line:95%,end
She wants it.

00:04:32.705 --> 00:04:34.173 line:95%,end
Why wouldn't she be the favorite?

00:04:34.240 --> 00:04:36.809 line:95%,end
Now, before I get started
on this week's assignments,

00:04:36.876 --> 00:04:38.611 line:95%,end
I want to ask Mackenzie
where your cast is.

00:04:38.678 --> 00:04:40.546 line:95%,end
You should have an air cast on that foot.

00:04:41.014 --> 00:04:42.782 line:95%,end
My foot doesn't hurt anymore.

00:04:42.849 --> 00:04:43.850 line:95%,end
And?

00:04:44.550 --> 00:04:45.718 line:95%,end
What's your doctor's excuse?

00:04:45.785 --> 00:04:47.153 line:95%,end
Did you go to the doctor again?

00:04:47.920 --> 00:04:48.588 line:95%,end
No.

00:04:48.655 --> 00:04:49.789 line:95%,end
I mean, yeah.

00:04:49.856 --> 00:04:50.757 line:95%,end
No, you did not, Kenz.

00:04:50.823 --> 00:04:52.358 line:95%,end
You didn't go back to the doctor.

00:04:52.425 --> 00:04:54.861 line:95%,end
Tell her exactly what the doctor told you.

00:04:55.461 --> 00:04:57.330 line:95%,end
He said that it's OK to dance.

00:04:57.964 --> 00:04:59.599 line:95%,end
And how did he look at your foot again?

00:04:59.899 --> 00:05:00.967 line:95%,end
He didn't.

00:05:01.367 --> 00:05:02.635 line:95%,end
So over the phone?

00:05:02.702 --> 00:05:06.372 line:95%,end
He said that she has to
rest it until it feels 100%.

00:05:06.439 --> 00:05:07.540 line:95%,end
She knows her own body.

00:05:07.607 --> 00:05:08.574 line:95%,end
She knows her own body?

00:05:08.641 --> 00:05:11.377 line:95%,end
She can't even create
a sentence to answer me with.

00:05:12.145 --> 00:05:12.979 line:95%,end
I'm sorry.

00:05:13.513 --> 00:05:16.749 line:95%,end
The doctor said two weeks
and I don't feel comfortable

00:05:16.816 --> 00:05:18.518 line:95%,end
going against his wishes.

00:05:18.584 --> 00:05:20.186 line:95%,end
It has not been two weeks.

00:05:20.253 --> 00:05:23.456 line:95%,end
I don't want Mackenzie dancing
because she's eight years old.

00:05:23.890 --> 00:05:24.824 line:95%,end
She's little.

00:05:24.891 --> 00:05:27.960 line:95%,end
Those tiny, little bones
in her feet are fragile.

00:05:28.027 --> 00:05:32.598 line:95%,end
And Mackenzie has the potential
to go the distance in her dance career.

00:05:32.932 --> 00:05:35.535 line:95%,end
I don't want to do something
now that's going to prevent her

00:05:35.601 --> 00:05:37.937 line:95%,end
from having a career
further down the line.

00:05:38.471 --> 00:05:39.706 line:95%,end
Let's talk about this week.

00:05:39.772 --> 00:05:44.610 line:95%,end
We are headed to Energy Dance Competition
in Youngstown, Ohio.

00:05:44.677 --> 00:05:46.879 line:95%,end
I'm sure that Kathy is going to be there.

00:05:46.946 --> 00:05:50.116 line:95%,end
I'm sure her boy group
will be back in full force.

00:05:50.183 --> 00:05:52.418 line:95%,end
But I'm really not too
concerned with Kathy.

00:05:52.485 --> 00:05:55.455 line:95%,end
I'm worried about the other
studios in Youngstown, Ohio.

00:05:55.722 --> 00:05:58.424 line:95%,end
The group number is entitled
to "Hear No Evil."

00:05:58.491 --> 00:06:02.662 line:95%,end
Everyone is in it,
except Mackenzie and Maddie.

00:06:03.896 --> 00:06:07.066 line:95%,end
Maddie, you will not be dancing with
the group in the group routine.

00:06:07.834 --> 00:06:10.703 line:95%,end
You will be assisting me
with the choreography.

00:06:11.838 --> 00:06:14.607 line:95%,end
I don't think the rest of the
group is as serious as Maddie.

00:06:14.674 --> 00:06:17.243 line:95%,end
They just say, well, Maddie
will figure out the counts.

00:06:17.310 --> 00:06:18.511 line:95%,end
Maddie will know the music.

00:06:18.578 --> 00:06:20.446 line:95%,end
So I want to teach them a lesson.

00:06:21.114 --> 00:06:22.048 line:95%,end
They all need to be the leaders.

00:06:22.181 --> 00:06:24.384 line:95%,end
They all need to know what's going on.

00:06:24.450 --> 00:06:26.352 line:95%,end
Maddie, you will be doing a solo.

00:06:27.053 --> 00:06:30.189 line:95%,end
The name of your solo
is "They'll Never Change."

00:06:31.224 --> 00:06:35.161 line:95%,end
Asia, you will be performing
a duet with Nia.

00:06:35.228 --> 00:06:37.330 line:95%,end
[applause]

00:06:37.397 --> 00:06:41.234 line:95%,end
The name of your routine
is "Move You Too."

00:06:41.300 --> 00:06:44.737 line:95%,end
And Asia, I'm expecting
my little firecracker

00:06:44.804 --> 00:06:46.072 line:95%,end
to light Nia up.

00:06:47.573 --> 00:06:51.277 line:95%,end
We're going to get Nia moving faster,
jumping higher.

00:06:51.344 --> 00:06:54.781 line:95%,end
Nia, when Asia's leg is up here,

00:06:54.847 --> 00:06:56.783 line:95%,end
her leg better be up there.

00:06:56.849 --> 00:07:00.987 line:95%,end
You can't be any less
than Asia is on stage.

00:07:01.988 --> 00:07:03.656 line:95%,end
It's going to be hard
for anyone dancing with Asia

00:07:03.723 --> 00:07:06.459 line:95%,end
to match her energy,
but Nia can hold her own,

00:07:06.526 --> 00:07:08.795 line:95%,end
and she can definitely
bring it to the dance floor.

00:07:08.861 --> 00:07:11.731 line:95%,end
I think Nia will be just fine
dancing with Asia.

00:07:12.031 --> 00:07:13.199 line:95%,end
I have one more solo.

00:07:13.733 --> 00:07:14.967 line:95%,end
It's going to Chloe.

00:07:15.034 --> 00:07:16.469 line:95%,end
It's contemporary.


00:07:16.536 --> 00:07:19.172 line:95%,end
And the name of the routine
is "About Mother."

00:07:19.705 --> 00:07:21.374 line:95%,end
Moms, you are dismissed.

00:07:21.441 --> 00:07:22.875 line:95%,end
Ladies, spread apart.

00:07:27.246 --> 00:07:30.183 line:5%,start
I'm taking you out of that group
because I think they're dragging you down.

00:07:30.249 --> 00:07:31.884 line:95%,end
And if you had a bunch of people
to dance with that were

00:07:31.951 --> 00:07:34.554 line:95%,end
on your level that wanted it,
you would be first place all the time.

00:07:34.954 --> 00:07:37.156 line:95%,end
You have to worry about you, understood?

00:07:37.590 --> 00:07:40.059 line:5%,start
Maddie's solo is called
"They'll Never Change."

00:07:40.760 --> 00:07:43.729 line:5%,start
Who is she referring to in "they?"

00:07:43.796 --> 00:07:44.697 line:95%,end
I don't know.

00:07:44.764 --> 00:07:46.732 line:95%,end
Maybe the other girls in the group.

00:07:47.266 --> 00:07:48.701 line:95%,end
Maybe they're not going to change.

00:07:48.968 --> 00:07:50.803 line:95%,end
Maybe they're not going
to try to work harder.

00:07:50.870 --> 00:07:52.939 line:95%,end
Or maybe it's the other moms.

00:07:53.005 --> 00:07:55.274 line:95%,end
Maybe they'll never change
and they'll always

00:07:55.341 --> 00:07:56.476 line:95%,end
be jealous of Maddie.

00:07:57.510 --> 00:08:00.513 line:95%,end
I think if Abby thinks that Maddie
is so much more mature

00:08:00.580 --> 00:08:02.181 line:95%,end
then Maddie should move
up to the senior group.

00:08:02.248 --> 00:08:04.450 line:95%,end
That's exactly-- then what's she
doing dancing with these kids,

00:08:04.517 --> 00:08:06.819 line:95%,end
week after week after week
if they're holding her back.

00:08:06.886 --> 00:08:07.720 line:95%,end
KELLY: Exactly. Move her out of our group.

00:08:07.787 --> 00:08:11.624 line:95%,end
If Abby thinks that Maddie is too good
for this group, pull her.

00:08:11.691 --> 00:08:13.259 line:95%,end
Have her dance with your seniors.

00:08:13.326 --> 00:08:14.327 line:95%,end
We don't need her.

00:08:14.393 --> 00:08:15.962 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:08:16.028 --> 00:08:16.863 line:95%,end
On your left.

00:08:16.929 --> 00:08:19.432 line:95%,end
8, 4, 5.

00:08:19.499 --> 00:08:23.870 line:95%,end
Maddie is demonstrating this week because
she's not such a second place performer.

00:08:24.403 --> 00:08:26.172 line:95%,end
She's a winner. She's a champion.

00:08:26.472 --> 00:08:27.373 line:95%,end
She's an artist.

00:08:27.440 --> 00:08:29.609 line:95%,end
She wants to do this 24/7.

00:08:29.675 --> 00:08:34.647 line:95%,end
It's totally unrealistic
and illogical to make it

00:08:34.714 --> 00:08:39.619 line:95%,end
so that Maddie is the only one that has
goals, aspirations, and everyone else--

00:08:39.685 --> 00:08:40.686 line:95%,end
And talent.

00:08:40.753 --> 00:08:43.122 line:95%,end
And talent and ambition.

00:08:49.362 --> 00:08:52.198 line:95%,end
The group routine is entitled
"Hear No Evil."

00:08:52.265 --> 00:08:54.000 line:95%,end
It's going to be a challenge
for the girls.

00:08:54.066 --> 00:08:56.736 line:95%,end
The music is difficult to count to.

00:08:56.802 --> 00:08:59.138 line:95%,end
So I'm going to pull their leader,

00:08:59.205 --> 00:09:02.842 line:95%,end
the one with the great musicality,
out of the group

00:09:02.909 --> 00:09:04.343 line:95%,end
and see how they handle it.

00:09:06.679 --> 00:09:09.715 line:95%,end
Every one of these girls
need to be the Maddie.

00:09:09.782 --> 00:09:12.151 line:95%,end
Melissa, are you comfortable with Maddie

00:09:12.218 --> 00:09:14.687 line:95%,end
being the assistant
choreographer of our group?

00:09:14.754 --> 00:09:18.124 line:95%,end
I heard her say she's
going to be assisting.

00:09:18.190 --> 00:09:20.493 line:95%,end
Yeah, don't be calling
her assistant choreographer.

00:09:20.560 --> 00:09:23.162 line:95%,end
What is the difference between
choreographing

00:09:23.229 --> 00:09:24.330 line:95%,end
and assistant choreographer?

00:09:24.397 --> 00:09:25.531 line:5%,start
What's the difference?

00:09:25.865 --> 00:09:27.533 line:5%,start
And it really doesn't
make a difference to me

00:09:27.600 --> 00:09:29.235 line:5%,start
if Abby pulls Maddie
out of the group dance.

00:09:29.302 --> 00:09:31.704 line:95%,end
I mean, Abby tells us every week
that Maddie is so much better

00:09:31.771 --> 00:09:35.007 line:95%,end
than our girls, so take
her out of the group then.

00:09:36.008 --> 00:09:37.710 line:95%,end
Asia.

00:09:37.777 --> 00:09:40.580 line:95%,end
But I have to say,
I know these girls have been dancing

00:09:40.646 --> 00:09:43.082 line:95%,end
together for a long time,
but I don't know.

00:09:43.149 --> 00:09:44.784 line:95%,end
Does she pick up choreography fast?

00:09:45.418 --> 00:09:47.520 line:95%,end
Right here in rehearsal, she might be--

00:09:47.587 --> 00:09:48.688 line:95%,end
